---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="American West Jewelry Case Study - Shane Boulos">
  <main>
    <article class="case-study">
      <header class="case-header">
        <div class="container-narrow">
          <a href="/work" class="back-link">← Back to work</a>
          <h1>American West Jewelry</h1>
          <p class="subtitle">Email Marketing & SEO Transformation</p>
          <p class="role">Director of E-commerce & Operations • 2022-2024</p>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section class="overview">
        <div class="container-narrow">
          <p class="lead">
            American West Jewelry, a heritage brand specializing in handcrafted turquoise jewelry,
            needed to modernize their digital marketing infrastructure while maintaining their
            authentic voice and customer relationships.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="key-results">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>Results</h2>
          <div class="metrics-grid">
            <div class="metric-large">
              <span class="number">124%</span>
              <span class="label">Increase in email revenue</span>
              <span class="context">Year-over-year growth</span>
            </div>
            <div class="metric-large">
              <span class="number">82%</span>
              <span class="label">Conversion rate improvement</span>
              <span class="context">Email to purchase</span>
            </div>
            <div class="metric-large">
              <span class="number">104%</span>
              <span class="label">Flow revenue growth</span>
              <span class="context">Automated customer journeys</span>
            </div>
            <div class="metric-large">
              <span class="number">#2</span>
              <span class="label">Google ranking for "turquoise"</span>
              <span class="context">Organic search visibility</span>
            </div>
            <div class="metric-large">
              <span class="number">52%</span>
              <span class="label">Spam complaint reduction</span>
              <span class="context">Improved sender reputation</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="narrative">
        <div class="container-narrow">
          <h2>The Challenge</h2>
          <p>
            When I joined American West Jewelry, the company was experiencing stagnant email
            performance and declining organic search visibility. The email platform was outdated,
            the customer segmentation was minimal, and the brand was losing ground to competitors
            in search rankings for critical keywords like "turquoise jewelry."
          </p>
          <p>
            Additionally, high spam complaint rates were threatening deliverability, and the team
            lacked the technical infrastructure to implement sophisticated automation and
            personalization strategies.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="narrative">
        <div class="container-narrow">
          <h2>Strategic Approach</h2>

          <h3>1. Platform Migration & Infrastructure</h3>
          <p>
            Led the migration from a legacy ESP to Klaviyo, rebuilding the entire email
            infrastructure with modern best practices. This included implementing proper customer
            segmentation, creating a comprehensive data model, and establishing technical
            safeguards to protect deliverability.
          </p>

          <h3>2. Flow Architecture & Automation</h3>
          <p>
            Designed and implemented an extensive library of automated customer journeys,
            including welcome series, browse abandonment, post-purchase nurture, win-back
            campaigns, and VIP progression paths. Each flow was meticulously A/B tested and
            optimized based on engagement metrics.
          </p>

          <h3>3. Segmentation & Personalization</h3>
          <p>
            Developed a sophisticated segmentation strategy based on purchase behavior, engagement
            patterns, product preferences, and customer lifetime value. This enabled highly
            targeted messaging that resonated with different customer cohorts.
          </p>

          <h3>4. SEO Foundation & Content Strategy</h3>
          <p>
            Rebuilt the site's SEO foundation with technical optimizations, strategic keyword
            targeting, and content improvements. Focused on high-value keywords in the turquoise
            and Western jewelry category, implementing structured data and optimizing for featured
            snippets.
          </p>

          <h3>5. Deliverability Management</h3>
          <p>
            Implemented comprehensive list hygiene practices, sunset flows for unengaged
            subscribers, and careful monitoring of engagement metrics to maintain strong sender
            reputation and inbox placement.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="narrative">
        <div class="container-narrow">
          <h2>Technical Execution</h2>
          <p>
            The transformation required coordinating across multiple technical systems:
            migrating customer data, integrating e-commerce platforms, implementing tracking
            infrastructure, and building robust reporting dashboards to monitor performance.
          </p>
          <p>
            I worked closely with development teams to ensure proper event tracking, built custom
            integrations where needed, and established data governance protocols to maintain data
            quality as the program scaled.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="narrative">
        <div class="container-narrow">
          <h2>Impact & Outcomes</h2>
          <p>
            The results exceeded expectations across every dimension. Email revenue grew 124%
            year-over-year, with conversion rates improving 82% through better targeting and
            personalization. Automated flows drove 104% revenue growth as the system matured
            and optimizations compounded.
          </p>
          <p>
            On the SEO front, American West Jewelry achieved #2 ranking for the highly competitive
            "turquoise" keyword, dramatically increasing organic traffic and brand visibility.
          </p>
          <p>
            Perhaps most importantly, spam complaint rates dropped 52%, establishing a foundation
            for sustainable long-term growth without risking deliverability or sender reputation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="narrative">
        <div class="container-narrow">
          <h2>Key Learnings</h2>
          <p>
            This project reinforced the importance of technical infrastructure as a foundation
            for marketing excellence. Without proper data modeling, tracking, and platform
            capabilities, even the best creative strategies will underperform.
          </p>
          <p>
            It also demonstrated the compounding value of automation—each flow improvement
            continues to generate returns indefinitely, making upfront investment in quality
            automation architecture highly valuable.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <footer class="case-footer">
        <div class="container-narrow">
          <a href="/work" class="back-link">← Back to work</a>
        </div>
      </footer>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .case-study {
    padding-top: var(--spacing-lg);
  }

  .case-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .case-header h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  }

  .role {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
  }

  .overview {
    padding: var(--spacing-xl) 0;
    background-color: #fafafa;
  }

  .overview .lead {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .key-results {
    padding: var(--spacing-2xl) 0;
  }

  .key-results h2 {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
  }

  .metrics-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--spacing-lg);
    margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);
  }

  .metric-large {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    text-align: center;
    padding: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .metric-large .number {
    font-size: 4rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .metric-large .label {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.3;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .metric-large .context {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
  }

  .narrative {
    padding: var(--spacing-xl) 0;
  }

  .narrative h2 {
    margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .narrative h3 {
    margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  .narrative p {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .case-footer {
    padding: var(--spacing-xl) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin-top: var(--spacing-2xl);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .subtitle {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }

    .overview .lead {
      font-size: 1.125rem;
    }

    .metrics-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--spacing-md);
    }

    .metric-large .number {
      font-size: 3rem;
    }

    .narrative p {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
